[[ 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:2360C094-A0AC-48DE-A5F5-D277750FE7A1" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Dasyatis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Dasyatis Rafinesque 1810:16" order="Myliobatiformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Dasyatis Rafinesque</taxonomicName>
]]
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="1">
The genus 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:2360C094-A0AC-48DE-A5F5-D277750FE7A1" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Dasyatis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Dasyatis Rafinesque 1810:16" order="Myliobatiformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Dasyatis Rafinesque, 1810</taxonomicName>
comprises 37 species and occurs worldwide (Compagno, 1999a,b and Gomes et al. 2000). Six species of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:2360C094-A0AC-48DE-A5F5-D277750FE7A1" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Dasyatis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Dasyatis Rafinesque 1810:16" order="Myliobatiformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Dasyatis</taxonomicName>
have been reported for the southwestern Atlantic (in Brazilian waters): the southern stingray, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:C1E79912-01EA-49F8-80AF-57CDBED430D8" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Dasyatis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Dasyatis americana Hildebrand &amp; Schroeder 1928:64" order="Myliobatiformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="americana">D. americana Hildebrand &amp; Schroeder, 1928</taxonomicName>
; the roughtail stingray, 
<taxonomicName class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Dasyatis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="centroura">D. centroura (Mitchill, 1815)</taxonomicName>
; the wingfin stingray, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:9BFB650A-97A8-40E6-BBEC-F80A830FDF38" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Dasyatis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Dasyatis geijskesi Boeseman 1948:38" order="Myliobatiformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="geijskesi">D. geijskesi Boeseman, 1948</taxonomicName>
; the longnose stingray 
<taxonomicName class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Dasyatis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="guttata">D. guttata (Bloch &amp; Schneider, 1801)</taxonomicName>
; the Brazilian large-eyed stingray, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:A530F01D-E290-4AD3-B125-D71E1D593CD6" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Dasyatis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Dasyatis marianae Gomes, Rosa &amp; Gadig 2000:510" order="Myliobatiformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="marianae">D. marianae Gomes, Rosa &amp; Gadig, 2000</taxonomicName>
, and the bluntnose stingray, 
<taxonomicName class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Dasyatis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="say">D. say (Lesueur, 1817)</taxonomicName>
. The other dasyatid stingrays known from Brazil are: the pelagic stingray, 
<taxonomicName class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Pteroplatytrygon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="violacea">Pteroplatytrygon violacea (Bonaparte, 1832)</taxonomicName>
and the chupare stingray, 
<taxonomicName class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Himantura" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="schmardae">Himantura schmardae (Werner, 1904)</taxonomicName>
(Dasyatidae) (Ribeiro, 1907, 1923; Figueiredo, 1977; Charvet-Almeida et. al., 2000, Gomes &amp; Gadig, 2003). The Atlantic stingray 
<taxonomicName class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Dasyatis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sabina">D. sabina (Lesueur, 1824)</taxonomicName>
, according to Garman (1913), has been recorded from North Carolina (USA) to Brazil. Bigelow &amp; Schroeder (1953: 376), cited the Brazilian record of this species, referring to it as &quot;... probably not on good evidence&quot;. Herein we describe a new species of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:2360C094-A0AC-48DE-A5F5-D277750FE7A1" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Dasyatis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Dasyatis Rafinesque 1810:16" order="Myliobatiformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Dasyatis</taxonomicName>
from 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Marajó">Marajo</normalizedToken>
Bay, state of 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Pará">Para</normalizedToken>
, northern Brazil.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
